<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Allow adapters to load multiple sections.</p>

<p>The section specification parameter in the constructor to be mixed:</p>

<h1>string - Names a single section to be loaded (currently supported)</h1>

<h1>array - Array of strings, which are the names of multiple sections to be loaded</h1>

<h1>null - Indicates that all sections should be loaded</h1>

<p>When multiple sections are loaded, first level properties would correspond with section names (e.g., $config-&gt;sectionName). When a single section is loaded, then the first level properties will be the first level of the data space of that section ($config-&gt;key1).</p>

